This paper discusses a mechanism for peer prediction markets, which is a topic related to game theory (cs.GT). The mechanism also involves using scores to measure the accuracy and reliability of agents, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of location information, which falls under the category of spatial information (cs.SI). Finally, the mechanism involves aggregating information from multiple agents, which is a topic related to data science (cs.DS).
